{
  "texts": [
    "Work related to development team formation is often obtained from open-source software development platforms with collaborative and social nature, such as Source-Forge and Kaggle.",
    "For example, Surian et al. [730] collected a dataset by analyzing the SourceForge database, which contained information about projects, project categories, and programming languages.",
    "There were 209009 developers associated with 151776 projects.",
    "The dataset included details such as 354 project categories and information about the usage of 90 different programming languages within the projects.",
    "Meanwhile, Ye et al. [732] collected a dataset by crawling data from Kaggle, including details from 275 competitions and 74354 developers."
  ]
}